onder why it doesn’t mark the dynamic report because there's no line. The user mentioned something about newly covered aspects being noted after direct reflection. Maybe it's because they ran the nativeTest instead of generating a dynamic report? I guess it'll depend on the attempts count, which might explain why direct reflection didn't cover certain dynamic logic.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_u9d1QuWyupFNbcsFkun0Hs1F|fc_0be187d71e5208cc016a0016f4e1d08192bdb7688384114ada", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured-common/5.5.0/src/test/java/io_rest_assured/rest_assured_common/AssertionSupportTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;\n\nimport io.restassured.internal.common.assertion.AssertionSupport;\n", "newText": "import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertSame;\n\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodType;\n\nimport io.restassured.internal.common.assertion.AssertionSupport;\n"}, {"oldText": "    void groovyDispatchCanResolveAssertionSupportClassName() {\n        String assertionSupportClassName = new StringBuilder(AssertionSupport.class.getPackageName())\n                .append('.')\n                .append(AssertionSupport.class.getSimpleName())\n                .toString();\n        AssertionSupport assertionSupport = new AssertionSupport();\n\n        Class<?> resolvedClass = (Class<?>) assertionSupport.invokeMethod(\n                \"this$dist$invoke$1\",\n                new Object[] {\"class$\", new Object[] {assertionSupportClassName}});\n\n        assertEquals(assertionSupportClassName, resolvedClass.getName());\n    }\n", "newText": "    void syntheticClassLookupCanResolveAssertionSupportClassName() throws Throwable {\n        String assertionSupportClassName = new StringBuilder(AssertionSupport.class.getPackageName())\n                .append('.')\n                .append(AssertionSupport.class.getSimpleName())\n                .toString();\n        MethodHandle classLookup = MethodHandles.privateLookupIn(AssertionSupport.class, MethodHandles.lookup())\n                .findStatic(AssertionSupport.class, \"class$\", MethodType.methodType(Class.class, String.class));\n\n        Class<?> resolvedClass = (Class<?>) classLookup.invoke(assertionSupportClassName);\n\n        assertSame(AssertionSupport.class, resolvedClass);\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2614, "output": 1856, "cacheRead": 45056, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 49526, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778390750109, "responseId": "resp_0be187d71e5208cc016a0016df684c8192b5868177c6e87f92"}}
